}

###############

terminal when (J_Begin) {
text: [[TTRS:notrans=
This is the vision that came upon me at the sight of that great edifice at the heart of our Garden, 
which is called the Tower of Babylon & the Tree of Knowledge▒▒ 
                            though its true name is Skepsis.▒▒▒▒
▓▓
   You were once a Giant, whose body was stardust & whose heart was a sun. 
   Your name in that time was ANTHROPOS.
▓▓
▓▓ Cast your mind back to that time now. ▒▒

]]
options:{
"TTRS:notrans=Remember" next: J_Remember
    }
}

###############

terminal when (J_Remember) {
text: [[TTRS:notrans=
Built across the galaxies was a great city that was called Jerusalem.
  This was the city of hope & dreams, 
  forever in motion, 
  changing with the drift of the nebulae in the solar wind, 
  yet retaining its essence. 
In that city all were citizens & all were kings. 

▓▓▓ Above all were valued ART, SCIENCE and WISDOM. ▓▓▓

But strife came to the city, and with strife came sickness. 
      (For sickness follows strife, and not the opposite, as some suppose.)

Thus you, the giant ANTHROPOS, fell into a feverish sleep
    and the city was torn apart
    ░▒ for the city is the PEOPLE, and the people are the CITY. ▒░

]]
options:{
"TTRS:notrans=Dream" next: J_Dream
    }
}

